title: Orange County Forum to honor former Gov. Pete Wilson
text:
Former California Gov. Pete Wilson will be the head line honoree today as the Orange County Forum celebrates 25 years of presenting monthly luncheons focusing on key economic, political and cultural issues.
Wilson, a Republican, served as governor from 1991 to 1999. At today’s luncheon, he also will be part of a panel discussing the utility of the forum.
“It’s to remind the community why O.C. Forum exists,” said Nancy Dooley, the event’s executive director since its inception.
The other scheduled panelists are former county Supervisor Gaddi Vasquez and Orange County Register publisher Richard Mirman. The Register is the founding sponsor of the forum.
The luncheon begins at 11:30 a.m. at the Hilton Irvine, 18800 MacArthur Blvd. Tickets are $125 at the door.
